    CameraCallback, LibUsbDevice, UvcContext, UvcDevice, UvcDeviceDescriptor, UvcDeviceHandle, UvcDeviceInfo, UvcFormatDesc, UvcFrame, UvcFrameDesc, UvcStreamCtrl, UvcStreamHandle, UvcStreamingInterface, VuforiaExternalProviderCameraFrame

    public class NativeObject<ParentType extends RefCounted>
extends DestructOnFinalize<ParentType>
    A NativeObject is the Java manifestation of some object living in native memory. We use reference counting to support the child-parent liveness relationships necessary when dealing with native child data that is allocated as part of a larger parent whole.
